# s.Dog Responsive YouTube Embed shortcode

## What the project does
Creates a Wordpess shortcode [sdog-youtube-embed src=""], where the src attribute is the URL of a YouTube video.  

## Why the project is useful
Copy an embed snippet from under the a YouTube video (click Share > Embed), paste into a Wordpress page or post, and it's not responsive out of the box.
to deal with that, add the shortcode above paste the URL into the src attribute.
**Note:** amke sure you copy the url with an /embed/ path, e.g. https://www.youtube.com/embed/DN6WTr9S6Rw otherwise your browser may throw an error.
The plugin stylsheet will make the resulting HTML responsive. [Credit where credit's due] (https://themeskills.com/make-embedded-youtube-videos-responsive-wordpress/) on the CSS came. 

## How users can get started with the project
Clone the repo and make whatever changes suit your task. To upload, you'll probably want to copy  via the Wordpress plugins 

